N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 1 ยง 195.2 - Mixed varieties

State Regulations
(a) Any
lot of grapes consisting of more than one variety which meets all other
requirements of "U.S. Fancy Table," "U.S. No. 1 Table" or "U.S. No. 1 Juice"
may be designated as "U.S. Fancy Table Mixed," "U.S. No. 1 Table Mixed," "U.S. No. 1 Juice Mixed."
(b) Unclassified. Grapes which are not graded in conformity with the foregoing
grades may be designated as "Unclassified."
